Newly launched stock exchange ZARX concluded its first trade in just 10 seconds. CAPE TOWN - Newly launched stock exchange ZARX concluded its first trade in just 10 seconds.ZARX was launched on Monday, providing the first competition for Africa s oldest stock exchange, the Johannesburg Stock Exchange, in more than 100 years.Last week, the financial services board ruled against the fourth and final hearing of a JSE appeal against granting the newcomer a licence.ZARX's CEO Etienne Nel says the response has been overwhelmingly positive . If you wanted an account with a broker on the JSE you d pay about R100 per month for a privilege, but in our environment it s for free and trade settles in real time. The first trade will match and clear off in 10 seconds. WATCH: How a stock exchange works(Edited by Shimoney Regter)